RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Special Weight Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOONSHINE MOLLY was kept close between rivals, moved to the rail into the bend, lost her path and was angled out leaving the turn, rallied two wide the last eighth and edged ahead inside the final seventy yards. REDHEADEDSTRANGER forwardly placed outside from the beginning, advanced three wide on the turn, rallied belatedly deep stretch but caught LASTCHANCESALOON for second nearing the wire. LASTCHANCESALOON soon edged ahead for the lead between rivals, took the rail with two furlongs to go, lengthened command upper stretch, began to wear down inside the last eighth but was easily best of the rest. BABAS GAL well placed from inside, did not keep up on the bend, angled outside REDHEADEDSTRANGER upper stretch and continued to yield. RICKY'S PART broke a step slow and somewhat awkwardly and was always outrun.

ENTRY.NAME: Babas Gal
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside turn, angled out upper stretch, flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Lastchancesaloon
ENTRY.COMMENT: speed between, angled in 1/4, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Moonshine Molly
ENTRY.COMMENT: kept close,angled in turn, angled 2 wide into stretch,got up late

ENTRY.NAME: Ricky's Part
ENTRY.COMMENT: awkward start, outrun

ENTRY.NAME: Redheadedstranger
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3 wide turn, best stride too late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Special Weight Purse 22000. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAPINYOURBLUEJEANS away slowly, gradually picked up his pace under hand encouragement, came into contention along the rail on the bend, angled outside with two furlongs to go, came into the lane from path four, rallied the final furlong, gradually lugged in deep stretch but caught HAND OVER MY HEART under a well-judged ride. HAND OVER MY HEART fractious in the gate, contested the pace inside rivals from the beginning, edged ahead on the turn, drew clear upper stretch but did not have enough left in the waning yards. SPICY DELIGHT vied for the early lead from outside, was three wide through the bend, angled in some upper stretch, still loomed a threat with a furlong left but leveled off instead. BEST MAN SPEECH was soon far back, picked up his pace some along the rail on the turn, angled out widest upper stretch and showed some late interest. WILDISH displayed early speed between rivals but began to fade before finishing a half mile.

ENTRY.NAME: Best Man Speech
ENTRY.COMMENT: far back early, saved ground, angled out stretch, mild bid late

ENTRY.NAME: Tapinyourbluejeans
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: away slowly, angled out 1/4, 4wide rally, lugged in late, got up

ENTRY.NAME: Hand Over My Heart
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious gate, inside speed, clear, not enough left

ENTRY.NAME: Wildish
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied between, 2 wide turn, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Spicy Delight
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied outside, 3 wide turn, angled in 2 wide stretch, evenly late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Claiming Races For $3,200 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FULL MAGAZINE stalked the early speed between rivals, angled in beside MY LITTLE TIPSY on the bend, drifted out to the middle of the track entering the lane, kept a straight path for the drive and drew off the final sixteenth. MY LITTLE TIPSY bobbled inward at the break, quickly recovered to set a pressured pace inside horses, was challenged on the turn, floated out to path three into the stretch, was no match for FULL MAGAZINE the last sixteenth, began to wear down in the waning yards but lasted for the place. STUMP forwardly placed from outside, progressed four wide on the bend, lost time moving outside FULL MAGAZINE upper stretch then rallied belatedly the last furlong. REMEMBER THE MAINE was a step slow and forced in at the start, settled outside, advanced three wide on the turn, fanned out to path five for the stretch run and made a strong move the final eighth between rivals. TROY OUNCE prominent just outside MY LITTLE TIPSY, began to yield on the bend, swung out to path four into the lane and failed to have a late bid. BACKSHOT was away slowly, raced in contention from inside but began to fade on the turn. INDIAN SIGN was a factor just off the inside but began to yield before finishing three furlongs.

ENTRY.NAME: Backshot
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: away slowly, saved ground

ENTRY.NAME: Indian Sign
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide, thru early

ENTRY.NAME: Remember the Maine
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced in start, 3-5 path turn, surged late

ENTRY.NAME: My Little Tipsy
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled inward start, inside 1/4, 3-path into stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Troy Ounce
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-4 wide turn, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Full Magazine
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide 1/4, drifted out badly into stretch, drew off last 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: Stump
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4 wide turn, angled widest upper stretch, closing

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Special Weight Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WILDWOOD ENOUGH shared the lead outside LIMANI, was roused midstretch and drew off as much the best. LIMANI broke on top, shared the lead from inside, was no match for WILDWOOD ENOUGH inside the final eighth, angled outside the latter nearing the sixteenth marker, drifted out further but was unchallenged for the place. CLASSY ACTION hesitated then swiped the gate breaking outward, was settled inside, picked up her pace after a quarter mile, two wide taking the bend, took over third nearing the eighth pole then could only hold her position late. MULSANNE (IRE) chased from outside, advanced three wide on the turn, drifted out some entering the lane and had no late bid. MOLLY'S TEMPLE in contention early, improved position two wide on the bend to move clear for third, fanned out some into the stretch and gave way. MO WANNA GO pressed the early pacesetters but faded from inside on the turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Limani
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, no match for winner, drifted out late

ENTRY.NAME: Mo Wanna Go
ENTRY.COMMENT: faded inside turn

ENTRY.NAME: Wildwood Enough
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated outside, 2 wide turn, roused 1/8, drew off

ENTRY.NAME: Mulsanne (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased outside, 3-5 path turn, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Classy Action
ENTRY.COMMENT: hesitated, swiped gate, 2 wide turn, bid, evenly late

ENTRY.NAME: Molly's Temple
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path turn, gave way

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Special Weight Purse 24500. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLYDE'S GREEN GO angled out two wide midway on the backstretch, took over when let out on the bend, widened command under urging upper stretch and was kept to task in the late going. SPAN reluctant to load, was void of speed, though hustled along from inside, angled out to advanced on the turn, came into the lane from path six, closed well and caught GOD GUNS N GUTS for second. GOD GUNS N GUTS chased while toward the outside on the backstretch, closed the gap four wide on the bend, moved clear for second upper stretch then leveled off in the late going. SHEBA'S PAL was bumped by RED ROIL then bumped with DENNIS'S PRIDE leaving the chute, chased from between horses, was two wide on the turn, improved position some upper stretch then also leveled off inside the final furlong. DENNIS'S PRIDE was bumped off stride from the rear at the break then bumped with SHEBA'S PAL, quickly recovered, steadily angled in as he vied for the lead, soon moved clear, was overtaken from outside on the bend and yielded through the stretch. RED ROIL was bumped at the start, forced inward and pinched briefly between horses, chased behind GOD GUNS N GUTS, angled in on the turn and lacked a stretch rally. NOBLE CREEKER raced widest of all and only passed a couple tired rivals deep stretch. ITS MAMBO broke a step slow and inward, bumped hard with DENNIS'S PRIDE, stayed well off the inside throughout and had little to offer for the drive. LATE BLACKSMITH broke inward, bumping RED ROIL, pressed the early speed, was three wide taking the turn then gave way between rivals through the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Clyde's Green Go
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide bid turn, drew off stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Noble Creeker
ENTRY.COMMENT: wide trip, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Span
ENTRY.COMMENT: reluctant to load, hustled inside, angled out turn, 6-path rally

ENTRY.NAME: Dennis's Pride
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped hard start, inside speed, faded

ENTRY.NAME: Its Mambo
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped hard start, 5 wide turn, no late bid

ENTRY.NAME: Sheba's Pal
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped twice early, 2 wide turn, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Red Roil
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped, pinched start, saved ground, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Late Blacksmith
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke inward, bumped, 3 wide turn, quit stretch

ENTRY.NAME: God Guns N Guts
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4 wide turn, weakened late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Claiming Races For $3,200 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ONE WAY HOME stalked the early speed from just outside, took the lead when allowed on the second bend, moved clear leaving that turn, drifted out under left-handed pressure upper stretch, held a straight path when switched to right-handed urging, widened command and proved much the best. KEEN RESPONSE bumped and forced out some at the break, was settled inside, gradually closed the gap on the backstretch and through the second turn, rallied two wide in the lane and gained second nearing the wire. ZARMAE chased from just off the inside, angled out on the second bend, came into the stretch from path four, took over second just inside the final sixteenth but was outfinished. CHERNYAHOVSKIY was a brief factor from inside, failed to keep up on the backstretch, was two wide on the second turn, forced out entering the lane, angled out widest upper stretch and showed late interest. PRINCE OF MAYHEM soon had the lead, showed the way off the rail, was overtaken from outside on the second turn and weakened inside rivals deep stretch. BOURBON DELIGHT broke outward, bumping KEEN RESPONSE, raced in contention from outside, moved to the inside with a half mile to go, floated out leaving the second bend and faded between horses.

ENTRY.NAME: Chernyahovskiy
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide 1/4, forced out into stretch, mild bid

ENTRY.NAME: Prince of Mayhem
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-path speed, no match for winner, weakened inside late

ENTRY.NAME: Zarmae
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-4 wide 2nd turn, had 2nd 1/16, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: One Way Home
ENTRY.OWNER: Martinez Ralph and Martin Paul E
ENTRY.COMMENT: roused 3-path 2nd turn, drifted out upper stretch, much the best

ENTRY.NAME: Bourbon Delight
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, angled in 1/2, gave way between foes stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Keen Response
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, settled, inside 1/4, 2 wide stretch bid, got 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 90. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 16000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TALIS PARK GRAD rated off the pace, advanced four wide on the bend, fanned out further entering the lane, took over nearing the sixteenth marker and drew off. FEVER NATION prominent from outside, moved clear for second just off the rail on the turn, stayed outside CAMPISI into the lane, floated out some upper stretch, was relegated to third approaching the sixteenth marker, regained the place with fifty yards left and narrowly held his position. TRY TRY AGAIN forwardly placed from inside, angled out some after two furlongs, came into the stretch behind CAMPISI, tried to gain a clear path to make his bid between the latter and FEVER NATION inside the last eighth, was checked briefly when his path narrowed in the waning yards then altered in to split rivals in the final strides. MON AMI FUZZIE pressed from between horses, did not keep up after a quarter mile, angled in midway on the turn and found best stride too late along the rail in the stretch. VIOLENZA D'ORO trailed from well off the inside, stayed in path four through the bend then made a strong but too late move the last eighth. CAMPISI edged ahead from between horses nearing the end of a quarter mile, drew clear and took the rail into the turn, came off the rail some entering the lane and wore down two wide inside the final furlong. ONE PUTT RICHIE displayed early speed between rivals, gained the rail nearing the bend, began to yield on the turn, was steadied briefly when his path was taken midway on the bend and continued to fade.

ENTRY.NAME: Try Try Again
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-path stretch bid, checked late, split foes

ENTRY.NAME: One Putt Richie
ENTRY.COMMENT: faded inside turn

ENTRY.NAME: Talis Park Grad
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated off rail, 4-5 path turn, drew off last 1/16

ENTRY.COMMENT: angled in turn, closing

ENTRY.OWNER: MCM Racing LLC and Gavilsky II Lawrence J
ENTRY.COMMENT: speed between, inside turn, weakened 2 wide stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Fever Nation
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed outside, 2-3 wide turn, held 2nd

ENTRY.COMMENT: 4 wide turn, late run

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 8 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 9500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEIRUT BEAUTY made a small leap from the gate, advanced from outside to share the lead outside LIFE OF SATURDAYS on the second bend, moved ahead when roused two wide with a quarter mile to go, was clear entering the lane, began to drift out upper stretch, steadily lengthened her lead while still drifting out, held a straight path inside the last sixteenth and proved much the best. LIFE OF SATURDAYS bumped with JERSEY GOLD at the break, vied for the early lead outside THINK BLUE, moved ahead on the backstrech, was challenged from outside on the second turn, was no match for BEIRUT BEAUTY when set down for the drive, gradually drifted out the final furlong but was unchallenged for second. THINK BLUE also bumped with JERSEY GOLD at the start, contested the pace from inside, began to yield before finishing a half mile, angled out on the second bend, came into the stretch from path four and could only pull away for third in the late going. MIKE'S LADY broke inward, chased from paths three or four and failed to menace. JERSEY GOLD was bumped from both sides at the break and never a factor in a ground-saving trip. HARD LIKE HOLLY a step slow at the start, altered in abruptly to avoid MIKE'S LADY, was then checked behind traffic and showed little.

ENTRY.NAME: Think Blue
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, angled out 2nd turn, 4-path into stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Jersey Gold
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped both sides start, saved ground, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Life of Saturdays
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, outside speed, inside 2nd turn, drifted last 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Hard Like Holly
ENTRY.COMMENT: altered in start, checked, outrun

ENTRY.NAME: Mike's Lady
ENTRY.OWNER: Lynch Harry E and Couch Ron
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke inward, 3-4 path, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Beirut Beauty
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped start, led 2 wide 1/4, drifted out stretch, much the best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 9 6F Dirt CR: 84. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Si nce August 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEEASY stalked the early speed from just outside, took the advantage on the bend, was roused leaving the turn, under urging in the lane and proved much the best. CRANKSHAFT set a pressured pace from path three, moved to the rail into the turn, was overtaken, no match for BEEASY in the stretch but was unchallenged for the place. SANTINO'S FANTASY was checked briefly behind BLOOMING GARDEN nearing the end of the first furlong, altered out, just off the inside on the bend, swung out widest into the stretch and gained third late. BUREAU was away slowly, advanced from outside to be a contender on the backstretch but began to fade four wide on the turn. LONESOME DREAM threw his head up just before the gate opened and was off somewhat slowly, progressed from inside on the bend then leveled off. LAYTON THE DAY forwardly placed between horses, stayed in path three through the turn and flattened out for the drive. BLOOMING GARDEN moved to the inside before finishing the first eighth of a mile and steadily faded soon after.
